Tourism Minister Mmamoloko Kubayi-Ngubane says tourist guides, tour operators, travel agents are allowed to operate under #Level3. JOHANNESBURG - Tourism Minister Mmamoloko Kubayi-Ngubane has announced which services will be permitted during alert level three of the lockdown. South Africa moves to alert level three of the lockdown from Monday, 1 June. Here is a list of permitted and prohibited services in the tourism industry; PERMITTED PROHIBITED - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs. Conferencing venues, festivals, casinos remain prohibited under #Level3. Courtesy #DStv403